    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "finding the number of cores the machine has physically is hard using purely Java.  Finding the number of cores the Java program can use at startup is easy, using <i>Runtime.getRuntime().availableProcessors()</i>.  Due to the ability of all major modern OSes to set CPU affinity (i.e. restrict an application to only a certain number of cores) this is a concern to keep in mind."
  }, {
